The linework was symbolized using the COASTBND attribute and visually inspected. Accuracy has been estimated to be 100% as of May 2000.
The final product was checked against the source material. The Mapping and GIS section of the Southwest Florida Water Management District corrected any errors found. There are no significant omissions.
Accuracy should meet National Map Accuracy Standards for a 1:2,000,000 scale map, approximately +/- 1000 meters.
In December 2003, the following Topolgy Rules were created and validated for the feature classes in the State and Water Management Districts feature dataset: Florida region must not overlap. Water Management Districts region must not overlap. Florida region must be covered by Florida boundary lines. Water Management Districts region must be covered by Water Management District boundary lines. The Cluster Tolerance was set at 0.005 meters. Any errors that were found were inspected and corrected using ArcMap 8.3.

state_cover created by the DEP from USGS DLG data
The UNIX compressed file was downloaded from the DEP ftp site along with the associated metadata. The file was uncompressed using the UNIX uncompress command. The export file was imported using the ArcInfo IMPORT command. The fuzzy tolerance was set to .001 and polygon topology was created using the BUILD command. The coverage was projected from ALBERS to UTM using the PROJECT command with the projection parameters listed below. The BUILD command was then used to recreate polygon and create arc topology. The ArcInfo commands ADDITEM and DROPITEM were used to modify the polygon attribute table (PAT) and arc attribute table (AAT). The following item was dropped from the PAT: MINOR1. The REGIONDISSOLVE command was used to create a region subclass called STATE.
The following projection file was used:
